<br>
Here is the point, we knew this was going to happen. We knew that there would be multipul problems with the whole new engine they planned on handing out to us with this expansion. I am surprised that the graphics are as good as they are considering the upgrade they just did. We bitched and moaned seeing how cool DAoC looked or AO for that matter, we wanted that, we wanted more. Well we got it, and frankly the game, in my opinion is fantastic. It works fine for me with the exception that I zone slow. Oh well, shit happens. <br>
<br>
The whole of it is...this wasnt sprung on us the day before, that we needed more specs on some of our computers. Going through alot of these posts and alot of your all running still on Win98 , it was never ment to take on 512RAM, that in itself is a problem, not VI's problem, your problem, microsoft made it that way, not VI. <br>
<br>
Okay so there are still ways to work around that problem and still use Win98, however any future games that come out, wont be compatable with Win98. Thats a fact that you are going to have to face. DAoC needs high specs to play, my old comp wouldnt play that either. Any new games that are coming out, older comps and programs are not going to play.Thats just how it is, my new comp will be outdated in a month, thats how the economy of it and how fast technology advances these days. <br>
<br>
We wanted more we got it, but at a price. One I was willing to pay, along with many others. Alot of us have been playing and dealing with the bugs of this game for a year and even more than that. You cant jump up and down and act naive about it all now. We knew the bugs and glitches and non play problems were coming with this.  The long and the short of it is, we knew the facts before they dropped it on us. Alot of us are hard core players, we know how it all works, that whatever new online game that gets released is not going to be perfect, how something works in Beta, is NOT going to work that way on the release program, no matter how we wish it that way.  VI is not stupid about this either, many will be attracted to the new aspects of this game, alot of defecters to DAoC are coming back, they have the systems obviously to play EQ Luc, VI anticipated this, they also knew they might lose customers to. You win some, you lose some, thats just how it is. <br>
<br>
Now of course you can flame away, if it was me having problems I would be screaming bloody murder<br>
